abstract: Hand gestures flashed by West Point cadets and Naval Academy midshipmen during the televised Army-Navy football game were not racist signals, military investigations have concluded.
snippet: Hand gestures flashed by West Point cadets and Naval Academy midshipmen during the televised Army-Navy football game were not racist signals, military investigations have concluded.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hand gestures flashed by West Point cadets and Naval Academy midshipmen during the televised Army-Navy football game were not racist signals, military investigations have concluded.
headline_main: Navy, Army Probes Find No Racism Intent in Hand Gestures
headline_print_headline: Navy, Army Probes Find No Racism Intent in Hand Gestures

abstract: Detectives solved the 1981 murder of a Florida woman by using advanced DNA testing to discover the suspect was the football coach of one of her sons, police said.
snippet: Detectives solved the 1981 murder of a Florida woman by using advanced DNA testing to discover the suspect was the football coach of one of her sons, police said.
lead_paragraph: LAKELAND, Fla. — Detectives solved the 1981 murder of a Florida woman by using advanced DNA testing to discover the suspect was the football coach of one of her sons, police said.
headline_main: New DNA Testing in 1981 Murder Leads Florida Police to Coach
headline_print_headline: New DNA Testing in 1981 Murder Leads Florida Police to Coach

abstract: The city of Baltimore will be monitored by surveillance airplanes for up to six months next year under a pilot program announced Friday that is aimed at helping law enforcement investigate violent crime and that will effectively restart a tactic secretively used three years ago.
snippet: The city of Baltimore will be monitored by surveillance airplanes for up to six months next year under a pilot program announced Friday that is aimed at helping law enforcement investigate violent crime and that will effectively restart a tactic s...
lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE — The city of Baltimore will be monitored by surveillance airplanes for up to six months next year under a pilot program announced Friday that is aimed at helping law enforcement investigate violent crime and that will effectively restart a tactic secretively used three years ago.
headline_main: Police Surveillance Planes to Fly Above Baltimore in 2020
headline_print_headline: Police Surveillance Planes to Fly Above Baltimore in 2020

abstract: Ten former colleagues of an Ohio hospital doctor who pleaded not guilty to murder in 25 patients' deaths are coming to his defense in a new lawsuit.
snippet: Ten former colleagues of an Ohio hospital doctor who pleaded not guilty to murder in 25 patients' deaths are coming to his defense in a new lawsuit.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — Ten former colleagues of an Ohio hospital doctor who pleaded not guilty to murder in 25 patients' deaths are coming to his defense in a new lawsuit.
headline_main: Nurses Defend Ohio Doctor Charged in Deaths at Hospital
headline_print_headline: Nurses Defend Ohio Doctor Charged in Deaths at Hospital

abstract: Palestinians welcomed the announcement, while Israeli officials erupted in anger.
snippet: Palestinians welcomed the announcement, while Israeli officials erupted in anger.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — The chief prosecutor of the International Criminal Court said on Friday that she had found a basis for investigating possible war crimes by Israel in the occupied Palestinian territories. But she is first asking the court to confirm that it has jurisdiction there, which Israel insists it does not.

abstract: In the background of a powerful photo of 15 black medical students from Tulane University is a slave cabin. In the foreground stand the students, wearing the white lab coats that tell observers they're members of a highly trained and prestigious profession.

abstract: President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
snippet: President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
headline_main: Pelosi Invites Trump to Deliver State of Union on Feb. 4
headline_print_headline: Pelosi Invites Trump to Deliver State of Union on Feb. 4

abstract: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
snippet: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi invited President Trump to give the State of the Union address on Feb. 4, a sign that business is operating as usual in the nation’s capital, even after the House impeached the president two days ago.

abstract: Government troops Friday captured four villages in Syria's northwest as part of a new ground offensive to push into rebel-held Idlib province, Syria's military and opposition activists said.
snippet: Government troops Friday captured four villages in Syria's northwest as part of a new ground offensive to push into rebel-held Idlib province, Syria's military and opposition activists said.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Government troops Friday captured four villages in Syria's northwest as part of a new ground offensive to push into rebel-held Idlib province, Syria's military and opposition activists said.
headline_main: Syrian Troops Make New Push Into Rebel-Held Northwest Idlib
headline_print_headline: Syrian Troops Make New Push Into Rebel-Held Northwest Idlib

abstract: More people are leaving California than moving in, evidence of the toll the state's housing crisis is taking as the world's fifth largest economy inches toward 40 million people.
snippet: More people are leaving California than moving in, evidence of the toll the state's housing crisis is taking as the world's fifth largest economy inches toward 40 million people.
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO, Calif. — More people are leaving California than moving in, evidence of the toll the state's housing crisis is taking as the world's fifth largest economy inches toward 40 million people.
headline_main: California Still Most Populous, but Stalls at 39.9 Million
headline_print_headline: California Still Most Populous, but Stalls at 39.9 Million
